https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lanpsy/article/PIIS2215-0366(20)30462-4/fulltext

Added to the fear of contracting the virus in a pandemic such as COVID-19 are the significant changes to our daily lives as our movements are restricted in support of efforts to contain and slow the spread of the virus. Faced with new realities of working from home, temporary unemployment, home-schooling of children, and lack of physical contact with other family members, friends, and colleagues, it is important that we look after our mental as well as our physical health.

The actual physical impact of COVID-19 infection on the brain leading to post infection mental issues such as post-traumatic stress disorder and other as yet unknown manifestations which are also affected by the prevalent pandemic situation and no end in sight. - Mod.UBA]

