Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 218.

Data by country, area, or territory for 10 Nov 2020 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20daily%20tablesNov11_1605176851.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 33.2% of daily case numbers and 21.9% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, maintaining its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 22.0 million cases. The USA is dominant, followed by Brazil, Argentina, Colombia, Mexico, Canada, Peru, and Chile.

- The European region reported 46.7% of daily case numbers and 57.9% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 13.8 million. Countries not reporting cases today (11 Nov 2020) include Israel, Sweden, Kazakhstan, and Bosnia and Herzegovina, among others. Countries reporting more than 10 000 cases in the past 24 hours include Italy, Poland, France, UK, Russia, Germany, and Ukraine. 21 additional countries reported more than 1000 new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 7.2% of daily case numbers and 10.2% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.40 million cases. Iran is dominant, with continuing record-breaking highs, followed by Jordan, Morocco, Iraq, Pakistan, Tunisia, Lebanon, and UAE. Libya, Kuwait, and Palestinian Authority each reported more than 500 cases but fewer than 1000, while Sudan and Yemen have not reported any cases in the past 72 hours.

- The African region reported 1.1% of daily case numbers and 1.9% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours and has reported more than 1.37 million cases. South Africa is dominant, followed by Kenya, Algeria, Ethiopia, Nigeria, Angola, Uganda, Cameroon, and Ghana. Countries not reporting any new cases include Madagascar, Botswana, Reunion, and Mayotte, and among others.

- The Western Pacific region reported 0.82% of daily case numbers and 0.46% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of 0.78 million cases. The Philippines is dominant followed by Japan, Malaysia, French Polynesia, Guam, South Korea, and China.

- The South East Asia region reported 11.1% of the daily newly reported cases and 7.6% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 9.7 million cases. As previously, India remains dominant, followed by Indonesia, Nepal, Bangladesh, Myanmar, Sri Lanka, and the Maldives.

Impression: It is very difficult to comment other than observe the continued dominance of Europe and the Americas region.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 11 Nov 2020, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

